                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">792.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/1–2254:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 414<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Thailand</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-19T15:59:00-05:00"
                            >February 19, 1954—3:59 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1646. Your 1524.<note n="1" xml:id="d414fn1">Telegram 1524, Jan. 22, conveyed
                        information regarding the estimated costs and procedures involved in the
                        proposed Saraburi-Ban Phai highway. (792.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1"
                            >MSP</gloss>/1–2254)</note> Saraburi-Ban Phai Highway discussed top
                    level <gloss target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> meeting Feb 17 by agencies concerned.
                    Agreed jointly (1) approve for planning purposes principle of highway
                    construction; (2) stronger reasons especially military required to justify high
                    enough priority to secure funds for financing; (3) imperative that Thai Govt
                    also ardently desire highway and accordingly make formal request through usual
                    channels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
